parent.title: Israel National Trail
parent.description: The Israel National Trail is a 1,100 km hiking path that was inaugurated in 1995 and was crowned by National Geographic as one of the world’s 20 best hikes. The trail crosses the entire country of Israel from north to south as it starts at kibbutz Dan near the Lebanese border and extends all the way to Eilat at the southernmost tip of Israel on the Red Sea.
